 and Waldau (seventeen kilometers); and it is at Waldau, by the bye, that the center of the land-selling enterprise is situated; a gaily painted pavilion, a fancy flag flapping, numerous yellow signposts: one, for instance, points “to the bathing beach,” but there is yet no beach to speak of—only a bog on the lip of the Waldau lake; another points “to the casino,” but the latter is likewise absent, though represented by something looking like a tabernacle, with an incipient coffee stal